<paragraph blockId="7.[178,1086,513,811]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">
C o m m e n t: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="EPPELSHEIM" authorityYear="1889" box="[363,618,513,534]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliqueseriatus">
<emphasis box="[363,618,513,534]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Quedius obliqueseriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally attributed to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="MULSANT &amp; REY, 1876" authorityName="MULSANT &amp; REY" authorityYear="1876" box="[178,521,544,566]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Sauridus">
<emphasis box="[178,268,544,565]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Sauridus</emphasis>
MULSANT &amp; REY, 1876
</taxonomicName>
, today a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="STEPHENS, 1829" authorityName="STEPHENS" authorityYear="1829" box="[817,1084,544,565]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Raphirus">
<emphasis box="[817,910,544,565]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Raphirus</emphasis>
STEPHENS, 1829
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="EPPELSHEIM E" box="[185,375,575,597]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" pagination="11 - 22" refId="ref7787" refString="EPPELSHEIM E. (1889): Neue Staphylinen aus den Kaukasuslandern, besonders aus Circassien. - Wiener Entomologische Zeitung 8: 11 - 22." type="journal article" year="1889">EPPELSHEIM 1889</bibRefCitation>
). The species was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="SOLODOVNIKOV A" box="[699,942,575,597]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" pagination="221 - 243" refId="ref8026" refString="SOLODOVNIKOV A. (2004): Taxonomy and faunistics of some West Palaearctic Quedius STEPHENS subgenus Raphirus STEPHENS (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 74: 221 - 243." type="journal article" year="2004">SOLODOVNIKOV (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, who did not explicitly assign it to a subgenus. However, according 
<bibRefCitation author="SOLODOVNIKOV A" box="[734,965,605,626]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" pagination="221 - 243" refId="ref8026" refString="SOLODOVNIKOV A. (2004): Taxonomy and faunistics of some West Palaearctic Quedius STEPHENS subgenus Raphirus STEPHENS (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 74: 221 - 243." type="journal article" year="2004">SOLODOVNIKOV (2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="SOLODOVNIKOV A" box="[975,1029,605,627]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref8062" refString="SOLODOVNIKOV A. (2005): New and little known species of Quedius from West Palaearctic [sic]. - Zootaxa 902: 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="2005">2005</bibRefCitation>
), it is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korge" authorityYear="1971" box="[365,498,636,657]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boluensis">
<emphasis box="[365,498,636,657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Q. boluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and some species described in the second paper (
<taxonomicName authorityName="SOLODOVNIKOV" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nonseriatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Q. nonseriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="SOLODOVNIKOV" authorityYear="2005" box="[312,405,666,688]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henrii">
<emphasis box="[312,405,666,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Q. henrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[421,439,667,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Q</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[455,543,666,687]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">humosus</emphasis>
), which he attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="STEPHENS" authorityYear="1829" box="[806,899,666,687]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Raphirus">
<emphasis box="[806,899,666,687]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Raphirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="EPPELSHEIM" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliqueseriatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Q. obliqueseriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[606,735,698,719]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microsaurus">
<emphasis box="[606,735,698,719]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Microsaurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in SCHÜLKE &amp; SMETANA (2015). Since 
<taxonomicName authorityName="EPPELSHEIM" authorityYear="1889" box="[246,438,728,749]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliqueseriatus">
<emphasis box="[246,438,728,749]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Q. obliqueseriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly closely related to the other species treated in the previous sections, it should be placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="STEPHENS" authorityYear="1829" box="[639,732,758,779]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Raphirus">
<emphasis box="[639,732,758,779]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Raphirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species is endemic to the 
<collectingRegion box="[178,355,789,811]" country="Russia" name="Krasnodar" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144">Krasnodar region</collectingRegion>
in the Northwest Caucasus (
<bibRefCitation author="SOLODOVNIKOV A" box="[646,871,789,811]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1144" pagination="221 - 243" refId="ref8026" refString="SOLODOVNIKOV A. (2004): Taxonomy and faunistics of some West Palaearctic Quedius STEPHENS subgenus Raphirus STEPHENS (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 74: 221 - 243." type="journal article" year="2004">SOLODOVNIKOV 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
